> This is a UI fix requested by the user. Correctness of logic (using `CustomMemoryMb` from [GameInstance](file:///c:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Models/GameInstance.cs#5-36)) is key.

## Proposed Changes

### [VersionSettingsDialog.xaml.cs](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/VersionSettingsDialog.xaml.cs)
-   **Modify [ShowSettingsTab](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/VersionSettingsDialog.xaml.cs#196-355)**:
    -   Add a new setting item: "最大内存".
    -   Implement a functional [Slider](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/VersionSettingsDialog.xaml.cs#451-492) (not the mockup [CreateMemorySlider](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/VersionSettingsDialog.xaml.cs#451-492)).
    -   Range: 1024MB to 16384MB (or 32GB if supported, stick to 16GB for safety).
    -   Step: 512MB.
    -   Bind `ValueChanged` event to update `_version.CustomMemoryMb`.
    -   Update a label text to show selected value (e.g., "4096 MB").
    -   Initialize slider value from `_version.CustomMemoryMb`. If 0, verify logic (LaunchService handles 0 as global, but UI should probably show global val or a default like 2048/4096).
        - If `CustomMemoryMb` is 0, setup slider to global default (e.g. 4096) or keep at 0?
        - Better: if 0, show "自动/全局", else show value.
        - Let's default to standard 4096 if 0 for editing, or read global? For simplicity, default to 4096 if 0.

